of draconic sorcerers. But the dragons' true heirs among the humanoids were the children born of a female dragon and a human father, who would spend their lives in a more permanent dragon-like form while growing no larger than their sire's humanoid proportions. This new race of half-dragon kin, as well as their descendants, became known as the Dragonborn.";}i:2;i:978;}i:27;a:3:{i:0;s:7:"p_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:2053;}i:28;a:3:{i:0;s:13:"section_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:2055;}i:29;a:3:{i:0;s:6:"header";i:1;a:3:{i:0;s:11:"Noble lines";i:1;i:2;i:2;i:2055;}i:2;i:2055;}i:30;a:3:{i:0;s:12:"section_open";i:1;a:1:{i:0;i:2;}i:2;i:2055;}i:31;a:3:{i:0;s:6:"p_open";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:2055;}i:32;a:3:{i:0;s:5:"cdata";i:1;a:1:{i:0;s:377:"Most Dragonborn bear their heritage proudly, and can trace their ancestry back to a specific chromatic, metallic, or gem dragon matriarch of their color. Their last names are usually the name of their ancestor, with family groups remaining involved (or at least invested) in the affairs of their forebear throughout the many generations since their dragon's initial conversion.";}i:2;i:2080;}i:33;a:3:{i:0;s:7:"p_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:2457;}i:34;a:3:{i:0;s:6:"p_open";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:2457;}i:35;a:3:{i:0;s:5:"cdata";i:1;a:1:{i:0;s:348:"Different species of dragons are predisposed to different patterns of behavior, and their Dragonborn descendants commonly show similar traits. Many dragons sit in positions of power or social prominence, and their descendants can often be found as high-ranking officials working for them or their organizations. Several examples are provided below:";}i:2;i:2459;}i:36;a:3:{i:0;s:7:"p_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:2808;}i:37;a:3:{i:0;s:10:"listu_open";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:2808;}i:38;a:3:{i:0;s:13:"listitem_open";i:1;a:1:{i:0;i:1;}i:2;i:2808;}i:39;a:3:{i:0;s:16:"listcontent_open";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:2808;}i:40;a:3:{i:0;s:5:"cdata";i:1;a:1:{i:0;s:478:" Amethyst and red dragons consider most other creatures to be lesser beings, available to be subjugated and used like livestock at their convenience. As far as one of these dragons are concerned, anyone within their chosen territory falls under their rule, and generally have little say in the matter. Appropriately-colored Dragonborn who show proper deference to their betters and prove to be useful can make quite the name for themselves in a red or amethyst dragon's service.";}i:2;i:2812;}i:41;a:3:{i:0;s:17:"listcontent_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:3290;}i:42;a:3:{i:0;s:14:"listitem_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:3290;}i:43;a:3:{i:0;s:13:"listitem_open";i:1;a:1:{i:0;i:1;}i:2;i:3290;}i:44;a:3:{i:0;s:16:"listcontent_open";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:3290;}i:45;a:3:{i:0;s:5:"cdata";i:1;a:1:{i:0;s:383:" Bronze and sapphire dragons share a militaristic streak, and have raised and commanded armies that few can rival. They often have a territory they base their campaigns out of, and are seen by the residents of these lands as their rulers and protectors. Bronze and sapphire Dragonborn with a military temperment can quickly rise through the ranks of these armies; if they can survive";}i:2;i:3294;}i:46;a:3:{i:0;s:6:"entity";i:1;a:1:{i:0;s:3:"...";}i:2;i:3677;}i:47;a:3:{i:0;s:17:"listcontent_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:3680;}i:48;a:3:{i:0;s:14:"listitem_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:3680;}i:49;a:3:{i:0;s:13:"listitem_open";i:1;a:1:{i:0;i:1;}i:2;i:3680;}i:50;a:3:{i:0;s:16:"listcontent_open";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:3680;}i:51;a:3:{i:0;s:5:"cdata";i:1;a:1:{i:0;s:248:" Preferring to inhabit the cold, harsh climates on the surface of the Istovian mountains, crystal dragons found themselves the accidental guardians of refugees of the church of Hroknar, who fled the mountain's underground cities after the church's ";}i:2;i:3684;}i:52;a:3:{i:0;s:18:"doublequoteopening";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:3932;}i:53;a:3:{i:0;s:5:"cdata";i:1;a:1:{i:0;s:12:"Great Schism";}i:2;i:3933;}i:54;a:3:{i:0;s:18:"doublequoteclosing";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:3945;}i:55;a:3:{i:0;s:5:"cdata";i:1;a:1:{i:0;s:234:" threw the now-fallen Istovian empire into civil war. Crystal Dragonborn with a stomach for geopolitical politics and the horrors of war in equal measure are considered invaluable to the Crystal dragons trying to stabilize the region.";}i:2;i:3946;}i:56;a:3:{i:0;s:17:"listcontent_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:4180;}i:57;a:3:{i:0;s:14:"listitem_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:4180;}i:58;a:3:{i:0;s:13:"listitem_open";i:1;a:1:{i:0;i:1;}i:2;i:4180;}i:59;a:3:{i:0;s:16:"listcontent_open";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:4180;}i:60;a:3:{i:0;s:5:"cdata";i:1;a:1:{i:0;s:547:" The powerful gold dragons assembled together after the Cataclysm, and allegedly spent months rigorously debating the best way to help repair the damage done to the world. They eventually decided to form an organization called the Shining Justicars, which was not beholden to any one region or group and patrolled the continent righting any perceived wrongs and meting out justice as they saw fit. Many gold Dragonborn have chosen to aid this organization as paladins of their order, acting as paragons of virtue and authority throughout the land.";}i:2;i:4184;}i:61;a:3:{i:0;s:17:"listcontent_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:4731;}i:62;a:3:{i:0;s:14:"listitem_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:4731;}i:63;a:3:{i:0;s:13:"listitem_open";i:1;a:1:{i:0;i:1;}i:2;i:4731;}i:64;a:3:{i:0;s:16:"listcontent_open";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:4731;}i:65;a:3:{i:0;s:5:"cdata";i:1;a:1:{i:0;s:356:" In order to preserve the continent's history, the emerald dragons created a repository of information called the Sage Vault, and established the Sages' Guild to discover and reclaim any history or knowledge they could find. Emerald Dragonborn commonly have an affinity for the kinds of scholarly and exploratory work involved in being a sage of the guild.";}i:2;i:4735;}i:66;a:3:{i:0;s:17:"listcontent_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:5091;}i:67;a:3:{i:0;s:14:"listitem_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:5091;}i:68;a:3:{i:0;s:11:"listu_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:5091;}i:69;a:3:{i:0;s:13:"section_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:5091;}i:70;a:3:{i:0;s:12:"document_end";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:5091;}}